    {
        "content": "<p>You want the <code>!₂[3, 4]</code> notation.</p>",
        "id": 507435736,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1742637154
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So typecasting to <code>EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin 2)</code> is not enough. What's the difference between <code>!₂[3, 4]</code> and <code>![3, 4]</code>?</p>",
        "id": 507435813,
        "sender_full_name": "Sabbir Rahman",
        "timestamp": 1742637235
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Doing <code>(_ : _)</code> is not actually a typecast, the type is used during elaboration of the term but is not enforced. Using <code>show _ from _</code> would be a typecast.</p>",
        "id": 507435950,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1742637338
    },
    {
